      {
        "id": 2216220,
        "name": "Tom Reddick",
        "username": "Tom_Reddick",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ecb155/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-10T02:56:32.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>2014 Domaine Jean-Claude Ramonet Bienvenue Batard Montrachet</p>\n<p>Opened 30 minutes prior to tasting, good young light lemon color, rich honeysuckle on the nose, citrus notes, lime, a good oak framing, on the palate magnificent- full lush cream notes leading into a mid-weight array of lime, citrus, white stone and mint notes, long and sleek on the finish, an hour later- the cream is receding and the citrus notes dominate, strong lime-driven acid finish, two hours later starting to close down and show some serious long term potential, still dazzling- but closing up, as fine a Ramonet Bienvenue as I have ever had, I think there is more sheer power here than in the 2001 though they are similarly forward in youth (at least for the first couple of hours), time will tell if this has the potential longevity of the 1996 when it is performing as it should- but I think this is one of the great recent examples of one of my favorite wines on the planet. Worth drinking one young if you care to do so- but if you do, be sure to catch it before it begins to close up. (*****), 2020++ I think it will come around some fairly soon but a good decade\u2019s wait for full maturity.</p>\n<p>2008 J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Riesling Auslese GK Auction - half bottle</p>\n<p>light yellow color, when first opened it was barely there, 90 minutes later a rich and yet finessed nose, a bit of petrol, marmalade, apricots, sweet citrus, on the palate an ethereal and elegant entry with a bright mid-palate impact, mandarin oranges, apricot, hints of pineapple, slight earth note and suggestions of dark plums, fine length, over the course of 3 hours it slowly built on the palate and finish but never lost its ethereal feel, impeccable balance, a very pretty finish with acids well hidden, coming around nicely but I plan to wait a few more years before opening another- this needs a bit more time. <strong>(</strong>*), 2020++ a very long life ahead.</p>",
