        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ecb155/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-11T02:54:22.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thank you both. It is always dangerous to declare something \u201cone of the best ever\u201d, and I appreciate knowing that two people more experienced than I share that view.</p>\n<p>I have not had a ton of 2014s, but the other two highlights for me besides Ramonet (Vergers and BBM so far- Caillerets and Morgeot left to taste) have been 2014 Thomas Morey Chassagne Montrachet Dent de Chien, and a truly beautiful 2014 Bouzereau Puligny Cailleret. That was my first Bouzereau experience and I was really impressed.</p>",
